<p>The Birmingham Natural History Society found the soft coral <hi rend="italic">Virgularia mirabilis</hi> while dredging near Oban, Scotland. They resemble <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi> specimens from Bahia Blanca, which draw themselves into the mud when touched.</p> 
